                  <P><STRONG><A class=3Dtcoutputheading id=3Doverview=20
                  name=3Doverview>Overview</A></STRONG></P>
                  <P>The OpenDocument Format (ODF) is an open XML-based =
document=20
                  file format for office applications to be used for =
documents=20
                  containing text, spreadsheets, charts, and graphical =
elements.=20
                  The file format makes transformations to other formats =
simple=20
                  by leveraging and reusing existing standards wherever=20
                  possible. As an open standard under the stewardship of =
OASIS,=20
                  OpenDocument also creates the possibility for new =
types of=20
                  applications and solutions to be developed other than=20
                  traditional office productivity applications.
                  <P><!--
        <p>The purpose of this TC is to create an open, XML-based file =
format specification for office applications.</p>
-->
                  <P>For more information, see the <A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/office/charter.php">TC=20
                  Charter</A> and <A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/office/faq.php">FAQ</A></P>
                  <P>The OpenDocument TC works closely together with the =
<A=20
                  title=3D"Visit ODF Adoption TC"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/tc_home.php?wg_abbrev=3Dodf-=
adoption">OASIS=20
                  ODF Adoption Technical Committee</A> which provide =
expertise=20
                  and resources to educate the marketplace on the value =
of the=20
                  OpenDocument OASIS Standard.</P>
