                  <P><A id=3Dodf10 name=3Dodf10><B>OpenDocument v1.0=20
                  Specification</B> </P>
                  <P>The <B>OpenDocument v1.0 specification</B> was =
approved as=20
                  an OASIS Standard on 1 May 2005. It is available in <A =

                  title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.0 in PDF format"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/12572/OpenDocum=
ent-v1.0-os.pdf">PDF</A>=20
                  and in <A=20
                  title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.0 in OpenOffice.org XML =
format"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/12573/OpenDocum=
ent-v1.0-os.sxw">OpenOffice.org=20
                  XML</A> formats.</P>
                  <P></P>
                  <P>The <B>OpenDocument v1.0 (Second Edition) =
specification</B>=20
                  was approved as a Committee Specification on 19 July =
2006. It=20
                  is available in <A=20
                  title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.0 (Second Edition) in =
OpenDocument format"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/19275/OpenDocum=
ent-v1.0ed2-cs1.odt">OpenDocument</A>=20
                  and in <A=20
                  title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.0 (Second Edition) in =
PDF format"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/19274/OpenDocum=
ent-v1.0ed2-cs1.pdf">PDF</A>=20
                  formats.</P>
                  <P><B>OpenDocument v1.0</B> has been approved as the =
ISO and=20
                  IEC International Standard <A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://www.iso.org/iso/en/CatalogueDetailPage.CatalogueDetail?CSN=
UMBER=3D43485&amp;scopelist=3DPROGRAMME">ISO/IEC=20
                  26300:2006</A>.=20
                  <P>The specification defines three Relax-NG schemas: =
</P>
                  <OL type=3Da>
                    <LI>The schema for office documents (defined in =
chapters 1=20
                    to 16),=20
                    <LI>the normative schema for the manifest file used =
by the=20
                    OpenDocument package format (defined in chapter 17), =
and=20
                    <LI>the strict schema for office documents that =
permits only=20
                    meta information and formatting properties contained =
in this=20
                    specification itself (defined in appendix A). =
</LI></OL>
                  <P>These three schemas are also available separately: =
</P>
                  <OL type=3Da>
                    <LI><A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/12571/OpenDocum=
ent-schema-v1.0-os.rng">OpenDocument=20
                    v1.0 Relax-NG Schema</A> (extracted from chapter 1 =
to 16 of=20
                    the specification)=20
                    <LI><A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/12570/OpenDocum=
ent-manifest-schema-v1.0-os.rng">OpenDocument=20
                    v1.0 Manifest Relax-NG Schema</A> (extracted from =
chapter 17=20
                    of the specification)=20
                    <LI><A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/download.php/12569/OpenDocum=
ent-strict-schema-v1.0-os.rng">OpenDocument=20
                    v1.0 Strict Relax-NG Schema</A> (extracted from =
appendix A=20
                    of the specification) </LI></OL>
                  <P><A id=3Dodf11 name=3Dodf11></A><B>OpenDocument v1.1 =

                  Specification</B> </P>
                  <P>The <B>OpenDocument v1.1 specification</B> was =
approved as=20
                  OASIS Standard on 2 February 2007. It is available in =
<A=20
                  title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.1 in OpenDocument =
format"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/v1.1/OS/OpenDocument-v1.1.odt">=
OpenDocument</A>,=20
                  <A title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.1 in tagged PDF =
format"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/v1.1/OS/OpenDocument-v1.1.pdf">=
PDF</A>=20
                  and <A=20
                  title=3D"Visit OpenDocument v1.1 in XHTML format =
(zipped)"=20
                  =
href=3D"http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/v1.1/OS/OpenDocument-v1.1.html.=
zip">XHTML=20
                  (zipped)</A> formats.</P>
                  <P>The three schemas defined by the OpenDocument v1.1=20
                  specification are also available separately: </P>
                  <OL type=3Da>
                    <LI><A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/v1.1/OS/OpenDocument-schema-v1.=
1.rng">OpenDocument=20
                    v1.1 Relax-NG Schema</A> (extracted from chapter 1 =
to 16 of=20
                    the specification)=20
                    <LI><A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/v1.1/OS/OpenDocument-manifest-s=
chema-v1.1.rng">OpenDocument=20
                    v1.1 Manifest Relax-NG Schema</A> (extracted from =
chapter 17=20
                    of the specification)=20
                    <LI><A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/v1.1/OS/OpenDocument-strict-sch=
ema-v1.1.rng">OpenDocument=20
                    v1.1 Strict Relax-NG Schema</A> (extracted from =
appendix A=20
                    of the specification) </LI></OL>
